{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PatternSpecRef\/PatternSpecProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"patternMatch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"stringLength","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"string","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!, "},{"text":"stringReversed","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">? = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Passing the correct","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"length of the string given is mandatory. The reversed string can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"omitted by passing "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", this is more efficient if the reversed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"version of the string to be matched is not at hand, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_pattern_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will only construct it if the compiled pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires reverse matches."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that, if the user code will (possibly) match a string against a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"multitude of patterns containing wildcards, chances are high that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"some patterns will require a reversed string. In this case, it’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"more efficient to provide the reversed string to avoid multiple","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"constructions thereof in the various calls to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_pattern_match()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note also that the reverse of a UTF-8 encoded string can in general","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be obtained by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.strreverse"},{"type":"text","text":"]. This works only if the string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"does not contain any multibyte characters. GLib offers the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.utf8_strreverse","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to reverse UTF-8 encoded strings."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"pattern_match is deprecated:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use [method@GLib.PatternSpec.match] instead","type":"text"}]}]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib19PatternSpecProtocolPAAE12patternMatch12stringLength0G00G8ReversedSbSi_SPys4Int8VGSgAKtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib14PatternSpecRefV","title":"patternMatch(stringLength:string:stringReversed:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"patternMatch","kind":"identifier"},{"te